description:
Come learn how to best optimize resume real estate with Katie Lindahl Smith, founder and coach at Careerable. Katie will also share how to utilize the experience you already have for any type of job. Just remember, the resume gets you the interview; the interview gets you the job. Learn ten easy ways to make the crucial first impression with resume real estate count. You’ll receive a custom resume template that is guaranteed to get a recruiter’s attention. 


Speaker Information 


 Katie Smith is Founder and Coach at Careerable, a career & talent development firm whose mission is to help individuals and organizations find their personal definitions of professional success. Prior to Careerable Katie worked at Salesforce and ExactTarget where her primary areas of focus included onboarding, career development, leadership development, performance management and college recruiting. Katie is serving as the 2015 Board President for Indy Reads and enjoys spending time with her husband and 10-month-old son.
name: Top Ten Ways to Optimize Resume Real Estate

description: This is the monthly gathering for Girl Develop It Indy! We welcome developers of all skill levels to discuss coding, upcoming classes, and other tech related happenings. Bring your laptop, and join in!  This is a casual setting and you are welcome to come and go as you please. *General Topics*--How did you get into tech?--Who inspires you?--What other tech groups are you involved in?--How do you stay motivated when learning to code?--What's your favorite website or programming language? Parking is available across the street at the Circle Center Mall garage (11 W Washington).
name: GDI Monthly Hack Night
